<item>
            <title>[LU-10255] sanity 129 wrong comparison operator used</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10255</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When sanity 129 is run the following error from bash is printed (this doesn&apos;t cause direct test failure): &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;./sanity.sh: line 9244: [: true: integer expression expected&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is due to has_warning being set to either true/false but those values aren&apos;t being evaluated as integers but as strings. So the correct comparison is actually: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; [ $has_warnings = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ] &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
